      "name": "FEA model ensemble accurately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending QoIs for non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct",
      "description": "The FEA modeling framework, comprising independent implementations by FDA, Ansys, and DePuy Synthes, produces predictions of construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement that agree with bench-test measurements within pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% relative difference on all QoIs; E/uval < 1.96 on each metric). This claim covers the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry under static compression-bending loading per ASTM F1717, as tested across two independent laboratories (N=11 constructs). The claim supports regulatory submission as evidence of model credibility at Medium risk level.",
      "scope": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm titanium pedicle screw construct; ASTM F1717 static compression-bending; quasi-static loading rate; room-temperature saline-bath conditions; two independent test laboratories",
      "purpose": "Establish that the FEA ensemble is fit for regulatory use in predicting compression-bending mechanical performance without requiring additional physical testing of design variants within the validated parameter space"
